HEADWORD: maidenhair berry
<hw>maidenhair berry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A slow-growing procumbent
evergreen shrublet (<spn>Gaultheria hispidula</spn>) of Northern North
America and Japan having white flowers and numerous white fleshy
rough-hairy seeds.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> creeping snowberry, moxie plum, <spn>Gaultheria
hispidula</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maidenhair fern</ent>⟦br⟧
